text: George Lascelles (by 1499 – November 1558), of Sturton and Gateford, Nottinghamshire, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Nottinghamshire in March 1553. ==References== Category:15th-century births Category:1558 deaths Category:English MPs 1553 (Mary I) Category:People from Bassetlaw District
